{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A file placed inside a subdirectory of the watched root is processed, not only files placed directly in the root directory.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"MOCK-MISS/REAL-INFRA: the failure boundary is real filesystem watch semantics (recursive vs non-recursive delivery from OS/watch library), not just local parsing. MOCK-HIDE: an in-process fake watcher can emit subdirectory events even when real OS wiring would miss them. ADVERSARIAL-CRITIQUE: this could be Integration if the watcher adapter already normalizes recursion and only internal routing is under test. TOP2-CONTRAST (runner-up Integration): behavior text says 'placed inside a subdirectory of the watched root' for a running daemon, which directly depends on real watch event propagation; System better catches that.","test_description":"Start the daemon against a real temp input root and output dir, create a nested subdirectory, write a file into it, and assert exactly one transformed output appears without restart. Use real fs events/end-to-end process loop.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.22,"System":0.75,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The deduplication logic correctly discards a second processing request for the same file path within a configurable time window.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"MOCK-MISS: this behavior is local dedup decision logic keyed by path+time window. REAL-INFRA/LLM-DEP/MULTI-STEP: none required. ADVERSARIAL-CRITIQUE: if dedup correctness actually depends on queue/storage handoff, Unit could miss an integration bug. TOP2-CONTRAST (runner-up Integration): behavior text focuses on 'deduplication logic' and configurable window, which can be validated in one object/function with a fake clock. REJECTION-GATE: System rejected because text does not require OS/network/subprocess behavior.","test_description":"Instantiate dedu